<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-06T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="265" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.96/324</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-06T23:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 6, 1918—11 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 6, 6.52
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>8928. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                            <p>No. 238. Our 157. At a meeting today with the British, French, and
                                Italians, the proposed draft was considered satisfactory as a whole.
                                I am sending a separate cable with a few suggestions which it is
                                hoped may be incorporated.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>